Andrew Cuomo has gone so far as to develop and start implementing an antibody testing system for New York State.
PolitiFact interviewed several experts about the promise and potential pitfalls of antibody testing.
Many antibody tests now being rolled out "may not be as accurate as we’d like," FDA commissioner Stephen Hahn has acknowledged.
The expected high demand for antibody tests should help push companies to do this quickly, he said.
It’s also important to note that antibody tests are just one part of what’s needed to restart the economy.